% Unification examples
% ?- [a, b, c] = [X, Y, Z].
% Output: X = a, Y = b, Z = c.

% Using the head/tail pattern to deconstruct a list
% ?- [Head | Tail] = [1, 2, 3, 4].
% Output: Head = 1, Tail = [2, 3, 4].

% A rule that uses pattern matching to get the second element of a list.
second_element([_, X | _], X).

% To query this rule:
% ?- second_element([apple, banana, cherry], Elem).
% Output: Elem = banana.
